<strong>REFERENCE LIST ENTRY</strong>
<br>
<br>
Add a reference list at the end of your essay citing all sources used in the body of your writing.
<br>
<br>
<strong>Format</strong>
<br>
<blockquote class="ref-hang-indent">
	<em>Book title.</em> (Year of publication). Publisher.
</blockquote>
<br>
<strong>Examples</strong>
<br>
<blockquote class="ref-hang-indent double-line-spacing">
	<em><span class="hover" title="Book title">Illustrated dictionary of medical and health sciences</span>.</em> 
	(<span class="hover" title="Year of publication">2017</span>). 
	<span class="hover" title="Publisher">Crosby&#45;Williams</span>.
</blockquote>
<br>
For a numbered edition, place the abbreviation in parentheses after the book title. This part should 
not be italicised. Use (Rev. ed.) for revised editions.
<br>
<blockquote class="ref-hang-indent double-line-spacing">
	<em><span class="hover" title="Book title">Illustrated dictionary of medical and health sciences</span></em> 
	(<span class="hover" title="edition">10th ed.</span>). 
	(<span class="hover" title="Year of publication">2017</span>). 
	<span class="hover" title="Publisher">Crosby&#45;Williams</span>.
</blockquote>
